# ğŸ¼ Pandas for Data Cleaning & Handling Missing Values

## ğŸ”¹ Overview
Pandas is a powerful Python library used by Data Analysts for data manipulation and cleaning. It provides data structures like DataFrame and Series to efficiently handle structured data. Real-world datasets often contain missing values, duplicates, incorrect formats, and inconsistencies, making data cleaning a critical step before analysis.

---

## ğŸ”¹ Importing Pandas
import pandas as pd  

---

## ğŸ”¹ Loading Data
df = pd.read_csv("data.csv")  
df = pd.read_excel("data.xlsx")  

---

## ğŸ”¹ Basic Data Inspection
df.head()        â†’ View first 5 rows  
df.tail()        â†’ View last 5 rows  
df.info()        â†’ Check data types and non-null values  
df.describe()    â†’ Statistical summary  
df.shape         â†’ Number of rows and columns  
df.columns       â†’ Column names  

---

## ğŸ”¹ Handling Missing Values

Check missing values:  
df.isnull().sum()  

Drop missing values:  
df.dropna()            â†’ Drop rows with missing values  
df.dropna(axis=1)      â†’ Drop columns with missing values  

Fill missing values:  
df.fillna(0)                   â†’ Replace with 0  
df.fillna(df.mean())           â†’ Replace with column mean  
df.fillna(method='ffill')      â†’ Forward fill  
df.fillna(method='bfill')      â†’ Backward fill  

---

## ğŸ”¹ Removing Duplicates
df.duplicated().sum()   â†’ Check duplicates  
df.drop_duplicates()    â†’ Remove duplicates  

---

## ğŸ”¹ Renaming Columns
df.rename(columns={"old_name": "new_name"}, inplace=True)  

---

## ğŸ”¹ Changing Data Types
df["column"] = df["column"].astype(int)  
df["date"] = pd.to_datetime(df["date"])  

---

## ğŸ”¹ Filtering Data
df[df["salary"] > 50000]  
df[(df["age"] > 25) & (df["city"] == "Mumbai")]  

---

## ğŸ”¹ Handling Outliers (Basic Example)
df[df["salary"] < df["salary"].quantile(0.95)]  

---

## ğŸ”¹ Exporting Cleaned Data
df.to_csv("cleaned_data.csv", index=False)  

---

